_pdbx_entry_details.compound_details           
;COMPONENT OF THE NADPH-OXIDASE, A MULTICOMPONENT ENZYME
 SYSTEM RESPONSIBLE FOR TRANSPORT OF ELECTRONS FROM
 NADPH TO MOLECULAR OXYGEN, GENERATING REACTIVE
 OXIDANT INTERMEDIATES. P40-PHOX ASSOCIATES PRIMARILY
 WITH P67-PHOX TO FORM A COMPLEX WITH P47-PHOX.
 NCF2, NCF1, AND A MEMBRANE BOUND CYTOCHROME B558 ARE
 REQUIRED FOR ACTIVATION OF THE LATENT NADPH OXIDASE
(NECESSARY FOR SUPEROXIDE PRODUCTION).
;
